label.value: decreased septum thickness

value.value: A septation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms a septum that is thinner than normal.

label.value: cell deflation and reinflation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell shrinks temporarily, but then recovers its original size.

definition.value: This phenotype usually results from a defect late in septum degradation.

label.value: loss of viability following cellular response to 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable after exposure to 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide.

definition.value: Use this term to annotate experiments in which a culture is grown in the presence of hydroxyurea, and then the number of cells viable enough to form a colony upon hydroxyurea removal is measured and compared to wild type.

label.value: decreased total protein level during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of protein measured in a cell is lower than normal during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: normal mitotic cell size control checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which a mitotic cell size control checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). A mitotic cell size control checkpoint normally prevents cell cycle progression until the cell reaches a certain size.

label.value: normal mitotic G1 cell size control checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which a mitotic cell size control checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). A mitotic cell size control checkpoint normally prevents cell cycle progression from G1 to S phase until the cell reaches a certain size.

label.value: normal mitotic G2 cell size control checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which a mitotic cell size control checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). A mitotic cell size control checkpoint normally prevents cell cycle progression from G2 to M phase until the cell reaches a certain size.

label.value: normal mitotic G1 cell size control checkpoint following nitrogen starvation-induced arrest in G1 phase

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which a mitotic cell size control checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell re-enters the mitotic cell cycle following nitrogen starvation-induced arrest in G1 phase. A mitotic cell size control checkpoint normally prevents cell cycle progression from G1 to S phase until the cell reaches a certain size.

label.value: normal mitotic G1 cell size control checkpoint following spore germination

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which a mitotic cell size control checkpoint is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in the cell cycle following spore germination. A mitotic cell size control checkpoint normally prevents cell cycle progression from G1 to S phase until the cell reaches a certain size.

label.value: mitotic G1/S phase transition at small cell size

value.value: A cell cycle phenotype in which the G1/S transition of the mitotic cell cycle occurs at a smaller cell size than normal after the cell has been arrested in G1 phase due to nitrogen starvation. The cell remains arrested in G1.

definition.value: A G1/S delay may indicate that a checkpoint, such as the cell size checkpoint or the G1/S DNA damage checkpoint, is activated. Checkpoint activation can be tested using checkpoint kinase mutants.

label.value: normal growth on vanoxerine

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing vanoxerine.

label.value: normal growth on hexestrol

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing hexestrol.

label.value: normal growth on clomiphene

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing clomiphene.

label.value: normal growth on ketoconazole

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing ketoconazole.

label.value: normal growth on terconazole

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing terconazole.

label.value: normal cell cycle process

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell executes a cell cycle process normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type). A cell cycle process is any of the processes that form part of the cell cycle, and thereby ensures successive accurate and complete genome replication and chromosome segregation.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: normal cell cycle phase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell executes a cell cycle phase transition normally (i.e. indistinguishably from wild type).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: normal onset of mitotic metaphase/anaphase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the metaphase/anaphase transition of mitosis begins at the normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) time relative to other cell cycle events.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleoplasm during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleoplasm is abolished during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to nucleus during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased DNA recombination at mitotic DNA replication fork barriers

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the frequency of DNA recombination at replication fork barriers is decreased.

label.value: decreased gene conversion at mitotic DNA replication fork barriers

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the frequency of gene conversion at replication fork barriers is decreased.

label.value: abnormal DNA clamp unloading

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the removal of a sliding clamp such as PCNA from DNA during replication is abnormal.

label.value: normal DNA recombination frequency at mitotic DNA replication fork barriers

value.value: A regulation phenotype in which the frequency of DNA recombination is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) at DNA replication fork barriers.

label.value: decreased number of Rad52 foci at mitotic DNA replication fork barriers

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates at or near replication fork barriers is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased number of Rad51 foci at mitotic DNA replication fork barriers

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad51 accumulates at or near replication fork barriers is lower than normal.

label.value: increased nucleus:cytoplasm ratio

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ratio of the nuclear volume to the total cell volume is greater than normal (the ration observed in wild type is approximately 0.076-0.089).

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'enlarged nucleus during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000344).

label.value: decreased nucleus:cytoplasm ratio

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ratio of the nuclear volume to the total cell volume is lower than normal (the ration observed in wild type is approximately 0.076-0.089).

label.value: nuclear membrane blebbing

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or both nuclear membrane(s) form blebs. Membrane blebbing usually leads to decreases in nuclear size and the nucleus:cytoplasm volume ratio.

label.value: sensitive to silver nanoparticles

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to silver nanoparticles. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of silver nanoparticles that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to butylated hydroxyanisole

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to butylated hydroxyanisole (BHA). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of butylated hydroxyanisole that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: sensitive to butylated hydroxytoluene

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to butylated hydroxytoluene (dibutylhydroxytoluene; BHT). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of butylated hydroxytoluene that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: resistance to butylated hydroxyanisole

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of butylated hydroxyanisole than normal.

label.value: resistance to butylated hydroxytoluene

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of butylated hydroxytoluene (dibutylhydroxytoluene; BHT) than normal.

label.value: normal cellular triglyceride level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more triglycerides measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: viable cell with normal cell morphology during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell has normal volume, dimensions and shape, and is viable, when subject to nitrogen starvation.

label.value: abolished protein localization to plasma membrane at cell division site during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plasma membrane surrounding the cell division site is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished lipid binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which lipid binding by a gene product does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: actin cables present in increased numbers during cytokinesis

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more actin cables than normal during cytokinesis.

label.value: asymmetric actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring contraction progresses in a radially asymmetric fashion.

label.value: asymmetric protein localization to actomyosin contractile ring

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actomyosin contractile ring is radially asymmetric.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased duration of protein localization to actin cortical patch

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to actin cortical patches for a longer time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal lipid binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of lipid binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal 3'-5' RNA helicase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of an 3'-5' RNA helicase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased ribosomal protein level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount on one or more ribosomal proteins measured in a cell is lower than normal.

definition.value: Also consider annotating to 'decreased translation of ribosomal proteins during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0004010), 'increased degradation of ribosomal proteins during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0004011), or both; bear in mind that either can lower the observed level of ribosomal proteins in a cell. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased lipid droplet formation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of lipid droplet formation is increased.

label.value: inviable swollen elongated multiseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, is swollen, is elongated, and contains more than one septum. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

definition.value: The distinction between this phenotype and centrally constricted (dumbbell-shaped) cells (FYPO:0000779) is that swollen elongated cells do not have a constriction along the long axis. Swollen elongated cells may have a uniform diameter, or may be swollen only around the nucleus.

label.value: protein mislocalized to cytoplasm during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is not normally found in the cytoplasm is observed there when the cell is subject to glucose starvation.

definition.value: Note that this term can be used to annotate any case where a protein is found in the cytoplasm in a mutant, but not in wild type. In some cases, there may be enough additional information to annotate to 'abnormal protein localization' (FYPO:0000443) or one of its descendants. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: normal protein level during glucose starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell that is subject to glucose starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Note that FYPO uses "glucose starvation" to refer specifically to conditions in which glucose is scarce enough to trigger mating, meiosis, and sporulation. For phenotypes observed in the presence of enough glucose to prevent cells from mating, use a term that specifies "during vegetative growth" plus a condition to indicate low glucose.

label.value: increased cellular S-methyl-L-ergothioneine level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of S-methyl-L-ergothioneine measured in a cell is higher than normal.
